<subSubSection id="9FE4C527DEEC0710A0FB831BE5740AE7" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="description">
<paragraph id="79243DFBC90F923E02487584F0CAEF64" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="129F087A5D2C8B1A317B30C9046F76CC" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Twining perennial of unknown height, stems with spreading yellowish trichomes. Leaves petiolate, 4.5-17 
<normalizedToken id="07D4BC08A08E7E8DA54E4D6C2A94B49A" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
3.5-14 cm, ovate, acute with a distinct acumen c. 1 cm long, cordate, appressed pilose with long hairs on both surfaces; petiole 1.5-10 cm, pilose. Inflorescence of pedunculate, axillary, few-flowered compact cymes, sometimes reduced to single flowers; peduncles 2.5-6 cm, bearded; bracteoles 1-1.7 
<normalizedToken id="6400E813E593353ABC78C3097BBE4CE4" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.2-0.3 cm, linear-lanceolate, mucronate, pilose, deciduous; pedicels 5-10 mm, pilose; sepals very unequal, pilose with golden hairs externally; outer bract-like, 13-20 
<normalizedToken id="1DC23CCCFE69C9D628CF5B711F3A880C" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
8-10 mm, ovate, cordate, acute, mucronate, middle sepal lanceolate, 11-13 
<normalizedToken id="4BFF997FEC0FB6150EE741BDA5F9426B" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
4-5 mm, inner linear, c. 9 
<normalizedToken id="E352F68AA748C3B761E36158CB9F2F0C" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2 mm; corolla 4-4.5 cm long, narrowly funnel-shaped, blue-violet, pilose with stiff spreading hairs, limb apparently lobed. Capsules and seeds unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
